[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1489},["Reactive",2],{"post-/posts/my-first-open-source-contribution":3},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"link":10,"date":11,"timeToRead":12,"tags":13,"body":16,"_type":1484,"_id":1485,"_source":1486,"_file":1487,"_extension":1488},"/posts/my-first-open-source-contribution","posts",false,"","My First Open Source Contribution","One of the things that I love about programming is that you can see a problem in the world and solve it. So when I found out that one of the apps I used on a daily basis was open source, I was pleasantly surprised","my-first-open-source-contribution","2023-08-06T00:00:00.000Z",6,[14,15],"Learn","Programming",{"type":17,"children":18,"toc":1481},"root",[19,47,70,75,105,110,115,124,142,147,218,223,449,454,496,520,691,711,804,809,847,875,1018,1030,1048,1289,1321,1326,1334,1339,1377,1382,1396,1475],{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":22,"children":23},"element","p",{},[24,27,36,38,45],{"type":25,"value":26},"text","One of the things that I love about programming is that you can see a problem in the world and solve it. When I had trouble getting into one of my college classes, I wrote a web scraper that would look at the class catalog for open seats and notify me when a spot came up so I could quickly register. When there wasn't a website for some niche Pokemon specific information, ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":29,"children":33},"a",{"href":30,"rel":31},"https://www.preethamrn.com/pokemondens/",[32],"nofollow",[34],{"type":25,"value":35},"I made one myself",{"type":25,"value":37}," (",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":39,"children":42},{"href":40,"rel":41},"https://www.reddit.com/r/PokemonSwordAndShield/comments/es50l6/update_interactive_map_of_the_wild_area_with_list/",[32],[43],{"type":25,"value":44},"and it went a little viral",{"type":25,"value":46},").",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":48,"children":49},{},[50,52,59,61,68],{"type":25,"value":51},"So when I found out that one of the ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":53,"children":56},{"href":54,"rel":55},"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.razeeman.util.simpletimetracker",[32],[57],{"type":25,"value":58},"apps",{"type":25,"value":60}," I used on a daily basis was ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":62,"children":65},{"href":63,"rel":64},"https://github.com/Razeeman/Android-SimpleTimeTracker",[32],[66],{"type":25,"value":67},"open source",{"type":25,"value":69},", I was pleasantly surprised. This app allowed you to track how you spent every second of your day. I love data and I love procrastination so this was perfect for me - I get to analyze how I spend my time and clamp down on the ways that I procrastinate mindlessly.",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":71,"children":72},{},[73],{"type":25,"value":74},"But there were 2 issues that bothered me:",{"type":20,"tag":76,"props":77,"children":78},"ol",{},[79,100],{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":81,"children":82},"li",{},[83,85,98],{"type":25,"value":84},"The date format used \"day/month\" instead of \"month/day\". I've lived in India and the US so I'm familiar with both and each have their merits",{"type":20,"tag":86,"props":87,"children":88},"sup",{},[89],{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":90,"children":95},{"href":91,"ariaDescribedBy":92,"dataFootnoteRef":7,"id":94},"#user-content-fn-1",[93],"footnote-label","user-content-fnref-1",[96],{"type":25,"value":97},"1",{"type":25,"value":99}," but I'm used to month/day right now so I wished there was a setting for it.",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":101,"children":102},{},[103],{"type":25,"value":104},"The app allows you to filter for activities in a specific time range. However, if an activity exceeds the time range then it doesn't clamp it to the specified time range. I don't need to know that I spent 30 minutes watching YouTube, 30 minutes reading, and 8 hours sleeping for the activities between 12am and 2am.",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":106,"children":107},{},[108],{"type":25,"value":109},"Now I could actually fix the