"props":1327,"children":1328},{},[1329],{"type":20,"tag":119,"props":1330,"children":1333},{"alt":1331,"src":1332},"Time taken","/posts/my-first-open-source-contribution/time-taken.png",[],{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":1335,"children":1336},{},[1337],{"type":25,"value":1338},"To give a rough timeline:",{"type":20,"tag":76,"props":1340,"children":1341},{},[1342,1347,1352,1357,1362,1367,1372],{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1343,"children":1344},{},[1345],{"type":25,"value":1346},"First I cloned the repo and got the application running on my device",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1348,"children":1349},{},[1350],{"type":25,"value":1351},"Then I used specific string and other details to find the activity and class where the relevant time formatting code was located",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1353,"children":1354},{},[1355],{"type":25,"value":1356},"I quickly replaced the existing time format with my own to see if this would fix the issue on my device. It did.",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1358,"children":1359},{},[1360],{"type":25,"value":1361},"I found all the places where the time formatting was referenced and ensured I didn't break any of those",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1363,"children":1364},{},[1365],{"type":25,"value":1366},"I removed my quick fix and instead locked my change behind a setting that could be toggled and added code that allowed users to toggle that preference",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1368,"children":1369},{},[1370],{"type":25,"value":1371},"I forked the repo, pushed my changes to a feature branch, and submitted a pull request",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1373,"children":1374},{},[1375],{"type":25,"value":1376},"The change was approved and merged.",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":1378,"children":1379},{},[1380],{"type":25,"value":1381},"All things considered the process went a lot more smoothly than I expected. I'm definitely going to contribute more in the future and I'd recommend you all to as well.",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":1383,"children":1384},{},[1385,1387,1394],{"type":25,"value":1386},"I mentioned 2 issues earlier but this post is already getting quite long so I'll leave it at that. Part 2 coming soon. If you want to get a sneak peak, check out the ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":1388,"children":1391},{"href":1389,"rel":1390},"https://github.com/Razeeman/Android-SimpleTimeTracker/pull/119",[32],[1392],{"type":25,"value":1393},"second pull request",{"type":25,"value":1395}," as well - slightly less likely to get merged but at least I'll be able to use the code for myself.",{"type":20,"tag":1397,"props":1398,"children":1401},"section",{"className":1399,"dataFootnotes":7},[1400],"footnotes",[1402,1410],{"type":20,"tag":1403,"props":1404,"children":1407},"h2",{"className":1405,"id":93},[1406],"sr-only",[1408],{"type":25,"value":1409},"Footnotes",{"type":20,"tag":76,"props":1411,"children":1412},{},[1413,1428,1441,1462],{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1414,"children":1416},{"id":1415},"user-content-fn-1",[1417,1419],{"type":25,"value":1418},"I say that each has their merits but if I'm being honest, I have no idea why you would use day/month. I know people say that it's better because it's in order - you go day/month/year from smallest to largest. But that means that when you try sorting days in lexicographical order, you get 11/01/2022 before 13/07/2005 which makes absolutely no sense. I think most people would agree than year/month/day is the best format because that sorts really well. And if you exclude the year then you get month/day which is perfect! And yeah month/day/year is a weird format too but at least if the year is all the same (eg. if you have a separate folder for all 2023 files) then you get the nice sorting property again. ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":1420,"children":1425},{"href":1421,"ariaLabel":1422,"className":1423,"dataFootnoteBackref":7},"#user-content-fnref-1","Back to reference 1",[1424],"data-footnote-backref",[1426],{"type":25,"value":1427},"↩",{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1429,"children":1431},{"id":1430},"user-content-fn-2",[1432,1434],{"type":25,"value":1433},"Step one was actually cloning the repo, installing Android Studio, fixing random issues with gradle, finding out that for some reason I was using a 32 bit version of Java in Android Studio, and making sure that I was able to even run the thing on my phone. But all that is less interesting than the actual process of diving into a massive, unfamiliar codebase. ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":1435,"children":1439},{"href":1436,"ariaLabel":1437,"className":1438,"dataFootnoteBackref":7},"#user-content-fnref-2","Back to reference 2",[1424],[1440],{"type":25,"value":1427},{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1442,"children":1444},{"id":1443},"user-content-fn-3",[1445,1447,1453,1455],{"type":25,"value":1446},"Most of the expedition was going through a bunch of different parts of the code to add a new preference for ",{"type":20,"tag":155,"props":1448,"children":1450},{"className":1449},[],[1451],{"type":25,"value":1452},"useMonthDayTimeFormat",{"type":25,"value":1454},", a new checkbox to allow toggling the preference, UI event hooks so that everything behaves properly when the checkbox is checked, and refactoring a bunch of method signatures so we're able to pass the preferences down to where they're actually used. ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":1456,"children":1460},{"href":1457,"ariaLabel":1458,"className":1459,"dataFootnoteBackref":7},"#user-content-fnref-3","Back to reference 3",[1424],[1461],{"type":25,"value":1427},{"type":20,"tag":80,"props":1463,"children":1465},{"id":1464},"user-content-fn-4",[1466,1468],{"type":25,"value":1467},"I double checked this after writing the blog and turns out it was even faster. Within 3 hours the pull request was reviewed and merged. ",{"type":20,"tag":28,"props":1469,"children":1473},{"href":1470,"ariaLabel":1471,"className":1472,"dataFootnoteBackref":7},"#user-content-fnref-4","Back to reference 4",[1424],[1474],{"type":25,"value":1427},{"type":20,"tag":1476,"props":1477,"children":1478},"style",{},[1479],{"type":25,"value":1480},"html.sepia .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-sepia);background: var(--shiki-sepia-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-sepia-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-sepia-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-sepia-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .sepia .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-sepia);background: var(--shiki-sepia-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-sepia-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-sepia-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-sepia-text-decoration);}",{"title":7,"searchDepth":259,"depth":259,"links":1482},[1483],{"id":93,"depth":259,"text":1409},"markdown","content:posts:my-first-open-source-contribution.md","content","posts/my-first-open-source-contribution.md","md",1703820234353]